wdump is a utility to dump word content into text or json.


Help

wdump: dumps contents of word document. 
Usage: wdump <file> [<option1> <option2> ...].
Options:
-u  : Transform returns to unix format.
-c  : Strip out carriage returns.
-j  : Output json representation of text, font, font-size, bold, and italic.

Using it without options will return a text representation of the text.

Dependencies:
It will only run on windows.
It needs to have Word installed.
